<HEADLINE>
FT  10 SEP 94 / Finance and the Family: Boost in demand for metals - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The encouraging growth in world economic activity is boosting demand for
metals such as copper, aluminium, lead and zinc, and minerals such as coal
and titanium dioxide - which gives the whiteness to paint, some plastics and
tiles.
All these are produced by RTZ, the world's biggest mining company, which
this week pleased the market by reporting interim profits at the top end of
analysts' expectations: a 30 per cent increase to Pounds 242m in earnings
adjusted to reflect the underlying business performance by excluding
exceptional items. The group, usually a conservative forecaster, also said
the global economic outlook had not looked as favourable since the 1980s.
