<HEADLINE>
FT  10 SEP 94 / International Company News: Anglovaal unit advances 18%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARK SUZMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JOHANNESBURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Anglovaal Industries, the industrial arm of Anglovaal, the South African
mining house, increased attributable profit for the year to June by 18 per
cent to R407.1m (Dollars 110.6m) from R343.7m for the previous year.
Pre-tax profits rose 8 per cent to R763.8m from R704.4m, but an 8 per cent
decrease in tax paid to R220.3m from R238.8m helped to lift bottom-line
earnings.
Turnover rose 16 per cent to R9.67bn from R8.32bn, of which 5 per cent was
the result of acquisitions. The dividend was increased to 230 cents from 195
cents. However, due to reduced cash resources and additional borrowings, net
financing costs on the year were R14.4m, a sharp reversal from the previous
year's R18m in net interest income.
