<DATELINE>
   OSLO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Serbia has accepted international monitoring of its blockade of rebel Serbs
in Bosnia and members of a 135-strong force are being deployed on the border
next week, according to Mr Jan Egeland, Norway's deputy foreign minister.
The force will check that no weapons or other supplies are getting through
to Bosnia from rump Yugoslavia, comprising Serbia and Montenegro. Monitoring
of the blockade could lead to an easing of United Nations sanctions against
Belgrade.
