<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / International Company News: Hotels help Brierley to post
record profit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Improved occupancy rates in London for the Mount Charlotte Thistle Hotels
helped Brierley Investments achieve a 58 per cent rise in profits to a
record NZDollars 430m (USDollars 259m) for the year to June 30, Mr Bob
Matthew, chairman, said yesterday.
Provincial hotel performances were also better, leading Brierley Investments
 -which owns 70 per cent of Mount Charlotte - to 'confidently expect
substantial improvements in Mount Charlotte's profitability'.
He said most New Zealand and Australian subsidiaries and associate companies
performed well during the year, with strong profit contributions from Air
New Zealand, Australian Consolidated Investments, textile group LWR
Industries, Sealord Products, Union Shipping and the Skellerup Group.
Subsidiary and associate company profit contributions were up 17 per cent to
NZDollars 318m from NZDollars 273m, and investment company contributions
rose 43 per cent to NZDollars 283m from NZDollars 197m.
Earnings before parent funding costs and overheads were up 23 per cent to
NZDollars 565m.
</TEXT>
