<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / International Company News: Macy merger deal approved by US
court
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A US bankruptcy court yesterday approved the merger agreement signed last
month by Federated Department Stores and RH Macy, two of the biggest
retailers in the US, writes Patrick Harverson in New York.
The Dollars 1.4bn deal to bring Macy's out of bankruptcy, however, still has
some hurdles to overcome. Later this month, a bankruptcy court will rule on
the joint reorganisation plan submitted to the court by Federated and Macy's
last week.
If that plan is approved, the merger is likely to go ahead, creating a
company with revenues of more than Dollars 13bn.
</TEXT>
