<DATE>940909
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / International Company News: Nine Network reports earnings
ahead 25%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Nine Network, the operator of Australia's largest commercial TV network and
44.5 per cent-owned by Mr Kerry Packer's Consolidated Press Holdings, has
reported a 25.5 per cent increase in profits after tax and abnormal items to
ADollars 88.3m (USDollars 64.9m) for the year to end-June, writes Nikki
Tait.
Revenues were up by 5.1 per cent, and operating profit before abnormal items
and tax was 11.5 per cent higher at ADollars 136.1m.
Nine said that its share of TV advertising revenue in the period amounted to
41.2 per cent, and that underlying costs - once allowance was made for the
Winter Olympics - had been static.
The company said that it expected pre-interest operating profits to increase
by about 10 per cent in the current year. However, it warned that profits
after interest and tax would probably not show any growth because of higher
interest costs incurred to fund increased investments outside its main TV
business.
Nine holds much of the Packer stake in John Fairfax, the newspaper
publisher; 18.08 per cent of Village Roadshow; and a 29.5 per cent interest
in New Regency, the US film production company.
</TEXT>
